A week ago, the draft stated that the oath should precede the signing of the decree.
The updated text states that Russia will be sworn in from the age of 18, not from the age of 14.
A rule has remained that the oaths shall be released to the incapacitated or the incapacitated, as well as those who cannot pronounce, read or sign the text of the oath by hand.
