“We will only be able to assess all the allegations made now after we have gathered all the information and been able to assess the situation.”
The Italian authorities have been monitoring the Juventa vessel, owned by Jugend Rettet, since October.
His crew is suspected of having taken migrants on board with whole lifeboats, which were sent directly to them by human traffickers, and allowed smugglers to leave along with boats that they could use again.
