The researchers believe that this herbivorous typhoon hit hard on what is now Canada until the spilled river took it into the open sea.
But the underwater burial of the dinosaur preserved its armor with precision to the smallest details.
The fossilized remains of this particular specimen are so well preserved that the remains of the skin still cover the bulging armor plates along the dinosaur skull.
