Previously, he was de facto engaged in the construction of the Vostochny Cosmodrome, but due to disagreements with the management of the Center for the Exploitation of Land and Space Infrastructure (CENKI), he was transferred to the enterprise in Moscow Filya, where he will coordinate production.
Mr. Ohlopkov will not have a shifter: the post of technical director will most likely be abolished, and the functionality will be deployed in the units of CENKI.
About the fact that the technical director of the Eastern and Deputy Director General of CENKI on technological development Andrey Ohlopkov went to work at the Khrunichev GKNPC, "U" told the top managers of several space industry enterprises, as well as an employee of the government apparatus.
“He has been working in a new position for several weeks,” the industry’s “U” interlocutors said.
It was not possible to get an operational comment from CENKI on Thursday, and Mr. Ohlopkov himself was unavailable for comments.
However, the information "U" was officially confirmed in the GKNOC.
He decided to move to the position of director for coordination of production, - said at the enterprise. - Andrei Ohlopkov has fully fulfilled the task set before him to ensure the launch minimum for the first launch at the East cosmodrome.
Mr. Ohlopkov moved to work at CENKI in 2013, having served in the space forces, in particular at Baikonur, and in Plesetsk - at the "northern" cosmodrome, held the position of first deputy commander in the rank of colonel.
In 2009, Andrey Ohlopkov became a member of the criminal case.
The investigation accused him of bribery: allegedly from his filing, regional merchants received government orders for the rollback, but did not fulfill the obligations to clean up the separate parts of carrier rockets in the Arkhangelsk region and the Republic of Komi.
In 2012, the jury found him innocent.
The technological development responsibilities assigned to it by CENKI extended to different projects, but the main one was the construction of a cosmodrome in the Far East.
The head of the then Federal Space Agency, Oleg Ostapenko, in an interview with “U” directly said that the situation in the East “was critical already in October 2013”.
The fact is that a strategic mistake was made during the planning: the completion of the construction and the first launch of the Soyuz-2.1 carrier rocket were planned for the same time - the end of 2015.
To carry out the launch before the end of the year, the completion of the construction was decided six months earlier and the deadlines were shifted from December to July 2015.
To speed up the process, it was necessary to go for a trick: the specialists of CENKI began to carry out parallel installation of technological equipment on unbuilt objects.
The main supporter of this idea was Andrei Ohlopkov.
Despite the existing risks and still the transfer (instead of December 2015 "Soyuz" flew only on April 28, 2016), this idea justified itself, says source "U" at the cosmodrome: "Otherwise, we would not have carried out any launches from the East, but would have been engaged in construction".
Deputy Prime Minister Dmitry Rogozin, who oversees the creation of the cosmodrome, jokingly called Andrei Ohlopkov his "cosmic Susanin", but it was he who almost always asked for information about the progress of construction.
Mr. Okhlopkov remembered straight: for example, in an interview with "U", he proposed to deprive the Federal Agency for Special Construction (Spetsstroy) of the status of the only contractor on the Eastern and directly work with subcontractors: "Why should we lay all the eggs in one basket?"
This idea was supported by the government.
Since 2017, CENKI has taken on the duties of a general contractor to complete the construction and installation work on the start-up and technical complex by the planned in the fourth quarter.
According to Y, the reason for Mr. Ohlopkov’s transition to a new place of work was disagreements with the leadership of CENKI about the ways to complete the construction of structures and complexes of the cosmodrome, as well as methods of working with subcontracting organizations.
"It was decided that this would be better for everyone," says one of the top managers involved in the construction of the Eastern.
An employee of the government apparatus, in turn, calls the decision strange: "He was one of the best specialists, finding him an equivalent replacement will not be easy."
According to "U", this will not be necessary: the post of technical director of the cosmodrome will be abolished, and its functions will be spread over the units of CENCI.
