In Venice, stricter fines for tourists for inappropriate behavior
The Venetian authorities have tightened fines for bathing in canals from 50 euros to 500 euros.
For walks around the city in a swimsuit or with a naked torso will now be fined 200 euros.
100 euros will be required from those who arrange a picnic in a public place or ride a bicycle in pedestrian areas, reports TASS with reference to the Association of Tour Operators of Russia.
In addition, it is mentioned that the authorities provide a fine for inscriptions on monuments 400 euros and for waste 25 euros.
Informing tourists about the need to comply with the rules of conduct in Venice will be with the help of a special company "Enjoy, respect Venice" (#EnjoyRespectVenice) in social networks, as well as through ads and posters on the website of the city council, on billboards and in places of the largest concentration of tourists.
The campaign will be conducted in 10 languages.
According to Venice Tourism Advisor Paolo Mar, information about the fines will be transferred to the embassies of the offending countries, in order to warn their compatriots of such errors.
“The problem is that Venice is perceived as a beach,” she said.
In April, the administration of the Italian city announced plans to limit tourist traffic.
Venice is already successfully operating a restriction on the number of tourists visiting the city center.
Instead of 100,000 people wishing to observe the Festa del Redentore festival, only 60,000 guests were allowed to the venue.
In addition, a moratorium on the creation of new hotels and fast food restaurants in the historic part of Venice has been introduced.
