Jazz in "Skolkovo": experiment and improvisation
The program of the second Skolkovo Jazz Science Festival, which will be held on August 26 at the Skolkovo Innovation Center, has been announced.
Guests are expected to perform by leading jazz groups and soloists, scientific discussions, interactive venues and other music-intellectual events.
As the organizers promise, the site will become a territory of improvisation and a field to demonstrate new creative opportunities.
“The guests of the festival will be able to immerse themselves in the world of experimental media technologies and learn how innovations in science become a new tool for interaction with art”, – Elena Zelentsova, Vice-President of the Skolkovo Foundation, described the focus of the forum.
Among the participants of Skolkovo Jazz Science 2017 are many stars, including the Moscow Jazz Orchestra of Igor Butman, who will present a joint program with vocalist Yaroslava Simonova.
Jazz and science are related concepts, and it is no coincidence that they have come together, - explained the folk artist "Izvestiam".
The experiment and improvisation of jazzmen are valued as highly as the scientists.
One of the main events of the festival will be the performance of Azekel, a British of Nigerian origin, known both for his own creativity and for his joint work with the legendary Massive Attack and Gorillaz.
Fans of the first jazz in Russia are looking forward to the performance of five-time Grammy Award nominee, pianist Christian Sands (USA) with his trio.
In the new capacity will try one of the best academic chamber orchestras "Music of Viva" under the leadership of Alexander Rudin and with the participation of pianist Yuri Favorin.
The fusion of jazz, ethnic and electronic music, as well as academic traditions will be demonstrated by the Marimba Plus ensemble and its leader, composer and marimba performer Lea Slepner.
One of the most unusual festival performances promises to be the set of the winner of the award Sergey Kurekhin Anton Maskeliadze.
An experimental artist manages music and video with gestures – that’s how leap motion technology works.
In total, eight music groups will perform on two stages of the festival.
In addition, the program includes open discussions, interactive zones and art objects, combined with the idea of a fusion of music and science.
Guests will be able to take part in experiments, visit a scientific buffet and observe the creation of cryo-glazed or flashing sands from debris and water.
In the special zone of vinyl you can buy records of current jazz performers and representatives of other musical directions, and at the book fair - publications on various topics, including musical, popular scientific and biomedical literature.
