Electricity is cheaper for both residents and commodity producers of Buryatia
The efforts of the Soviet and post-Soviet authorities of the Republic of Buryatia (Eastern Siberia) to establish fair tariffs for electricity consumers have been paying off for more than a decade.
Since September 1, the cost of low-voltage electricity for industrial recipients has been reduced by 25%.
The Federal Antimonopoly Service of the country in accordance with the Decree of the Government of the Russian Federation "On Amendments to the Rules of the Wholesale Market of Electricity and Power and to the Consolidated Forecast Balance of Production and Supply of Electricity (Power) within the Unified Energy System of Russia for the Subjects of the Russian Federation" (No.
As a result, the cost of electricity for Buryat commodity producers is reduced by a quarter, which will greatly facilitate the life of small and medium-sized enterprises and individual entrepreneurs.
For decades, the leaders of the republic have broken the thresholds of the Moscow cabinets in vain attempts to level the region in tariffs from the neighboring Irkutsk region with a cascade of hydroelectric plants on Angara, flowing from Baikal, the main catchment area for which is Buryat.
It was only this year that the movement began.
In March, electricity tariffs for the population of the republic were reduced from 4.24 rubles/kWh to 3.93 rubles/kWh, or 7.3%.
With the inclusion of Buryatia by the decision of the federal government in the List of territories of wholesale market price zones, for which the peculiarities of the functioning of wholesale and retail markets are established, a turn of industrial consumers has occurred.
According to analysts, this is only the beginning, since the population of the Irkutsk region pays per kilowatt hour 1.01 rubles.
But no one dares to name at least the approximate date of the new tariff movements in the direction of the decline for Buryatia.
