In Ukraine proposed to send Russians to prison for illegal crossing of the border
The Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine has registered a draft law according to which in the republic there may be a criminal penalty for Russians for illegal crossing of the Ukrainian border.
According to RT, a document registered in the electronic database of the Ukrainian parliament envisages a three-year prison sentence for Russian citizens trying to illegally enter the country.
It is noted that for a repeated offence or act committed by a group of persons, the term of imprisonment may be increased to five years.
If the offender was detained at the border with a weapon, the time of detention for him will increase to eight years.
Earlier it was reported that Ukrainian border guards detained Ukrainians who were trying to get into Russia outside the established checkpoints.
