In Russia, there will be two new territories of advanced socio-economic development - "Abaza" and "Novotroitsk".
The relevant decrees of the Government of the Russian Federation will enter into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activity of the TOR on the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Khakassia are defined.
In the city, where 15,000 people live, there will be a special legal regime of business activity, as well as the minimum amount of capital investments of residents, the minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investment in the city, and will create more than 600 new jobs.
The list of economic activities in which the TOR "Abaza" will have a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity, for example, includes plant breeding, animal husbandry, production of food, soft drinks and clothing.
Already now, the Government of the Republic has signed framework agreements on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the territory on the city-forming enterprise "Abakan Mining".
In January 2017, the authorities of the region reported that Khakassia fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development for the creation of the TOR.
The authorities of the Orenburg region did the same.
There, in the city of Novotroitsk, a territory of advanced socio-economic development will also be created.
This will allow to diversify the economy of the monocity, reduce its dependence on the city-forming enterprise of JSC Ural Steel, as well as create more than 2.3 thousand jobs and attract investments in the amount of more than 8 billion rubles.
The list of economic activities in which the new TOR will have a special legal regime for entrepreneurs includes, in particular, freshwater fishing, the production of feed, medicines and medical materials.
Novotroitsk became the first of the Orenburg region’s monocities to receive TOR status.
Recall that the territory of advanced development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investment to improve the life of the population.
Among the benefits for residents of TOR can be distinguished the following: a profit tax of not more than 5% during the first five years, and not less than 10% during the next 5 years, social contributions of 7.6% for 10 years, the use of the free customs zone regime, a preferential mode of connection to various facilities of infrastructure, as well as a preferential rate.
