In Moscow, a policeman wounded a man in the leg, protecting himself from attack
A policeman shot a participant in a fight in Moscow after he attacked him with a piece of glass in his hand.
On the evening of August 3, the police department of the Russian Ministry of Internal Affairs in the Yakimanka district received a message about the fight on 46 Mytna Street.
"The arrived police uniform stopped the crime and took away the participants of the conflict," RIA Novosti reported, referring to the press service of the capital's head of the Ministry of Internal Affairs.
According to the police, when one of the participants in the conflict attacked an employee of the Ministry of Interior with a piece of glass, the policeman several times warned the man about the use of weapons and made a warning shot.
This did not stop the hooligan, after which a law enforcement officer shot a man in the leg.
The injured man was in need of hospitalization.
